{title:'Process Tracing: From Metaphor to Analytic Tool',author:'Bennett & Checkel, eds.',year:2015,type:'Methods Text',tradition:'General',desc:'State-of-the-art volume on process tracing methods. Includes chapters on Bayesian reasoning, evidence evaluation, and practical applications.'},
{title:'Process-Tracing Methods',author:'Beach & Pedersen',year:2013,type:'Methods Text',tradition:'General',desc:'Distinguishes three variants of process tracing. Practical guidance on mechanism identification and evidence.'},
{title:'Doing Feminist Research in Political and Social Science',author:'Ackerly & True',year:2010,type:'Methods Text',tradition:'Critical',desc:'Shows how feminist commitments shape every stage of research design. Essential for critical and feminist IR students.'},
{title:'Social Forces, States and World Orders',author:'Cox, Robert',year:1981,type:'Exemplary Work',tradition:'Critical',desc:'"Theory is always for someone and for some purpose." Foundational statement distinguishing critical from problem-solving theory.'},
{title:'Anarchy is What States Make of It',author:'Wendt, Alexander',year:1992,type:'Exemplary Work',tradition:'Interpretivist',desc:'The article that launched constructivism in IR. Challenges neorealist claims about anarchy being structurally determined.'},
